<br>
Of course, you can't really browse like a real bookstore, but it's still a fantastic innovation.  It's especially nice if you're like me and buy a lot of really eclectic or technical books.  I used to have to drive into New York (either McGraw-Hill or the technical B&amp;N downtown on 17th street) from Connecticut when I was younger to buy the books I wanted.<br>
